values: This conversation we're having, this very moment, is crap. And I'm waiting for you to say something with substance... & you probably won't, & it'll probably trail off into nothing... & you'll probably make an excuse to leave... & I'll probably accept it & do the same. Because we can't just say, "IM SORRY. I MISS YOU."

Just heard the leak of the first single from Weezer's untitled seventh album. Not real impressed, but it could've been worse. Weezer keeps re-inventing themselves and it's sort of this on-again, off-again relationship I have with them. Give me blue, green, Pinkerton and yeah, sure, even the red album. Keep Maladroit (though I'm on the fence about that adorable "Keep Fishin" video), and you know what?, just go ahead and burn that Make Believe bullshit. Weezer is comfort food for my ears, so I kind of cross my fingers for them each time, yaknow?







GUESS WE'LL SEE.

I'm now the proud mama of my first bonsai tree! Meowwwww! Sorry if you haven't received your mail yet from me, I'm a little tight on money until this new job kicks in. Lots of exciting things are happening in the next few months, 2009 will wrap up pretty damn good.

Autumn/Fall, are you here yet? You know you're my favorite.

We were good, we have memories. We've brought drama, we've brought chaos. We've settled down and then I got sick of you. And after five long years, I tried to say goodbye to you. And it's not that I missed you, because I didn't, and I don't. It's because I'm used to you. You're the only thing I'll keep because I'm comfortable. What I said about never coming back to you? I lied and I'm sorry. You're cute and you do nothing but shut the fuck up and listen. More people should follow in your footsteps.

Love you still (for now),
KMR

<center><lj-embed id="16"/>



You either hang with me or you don't.
I might just post Will Smith music videos from now on.

Sometimes, I wish my friends would put more of their life decisions in my hand. Not saying they can't handle themselves. I'm saying I'd make better ones for them. Better ones in my opinion. Like who they're dating, what they're doing, where they are or even where they're headed. A lot of my social frustration is in the department of seeing my friends make (once again, in my opinion) poor decisions.
I mean, I think I'm being a fair friend by letting them handle it themselves and even supporting them. I think I'm being a fair friend by also staying true to myself and saying, "I love you man, but the fuck?"


................ if ya'll would just let me, I'd turn the world on for you.

I work at Ping Pong, the hippest japanese restaurant in Chicago. I have a huge apartment with four very fun roommates. I saw Animal Collective on Monday and it was absolutely awesome. I had so much fun. I seriously love it here. I miss my ladies, but the weekend was pleasant to have spent a night with them. I don't really miss Mount Pleasant, but it was my hometown. I am happy and things are getting better and better.

w/ my ladies, my homegirls.
i couldn't be more excited right now.
tomorrorororowowwwwww

I have been sick all wknd. I miss the warm weather and I can't wait for March22 and 27th. I am seriously going to have the time of my life and end my reign in Michigan the best way possible.

So long, Steebs. Your party was fun.

I am so excited for March. So many plans and lots of girls nights out, which never happen besides just having a few drinks and watching a movie. (Not that I'm complaining, really...) Ratatat in 20 days and Funk Night a few days after that. I am excited for Funk Night to finally happen. Every single time, my ride/friend flakes out last minute and I end up bitter and bratty. Friday night, I was the drunkest I've been in years. I was loud and rude and dancing my little heart out. All of my friends played hero when I hermit'd on the staircase to try to stop the spins from intensifying. Not my proudest action, but was real fun nonetheless. I made some art and am starting my clothing website next week, hopefully up and running by the end of the month. Monnaaaayyy $$$$$

♥

"I saw God in the trees, it's lovely, but its lonely. With a bone, he will try to clone me- make a mother... there will be another me. [your mom] when the bomb exploded, overloaded, eaten fruit birthday suit decoded. I decided you would like another mom. Bomb, bomb, bomb. Marry me, lucky tree. You're my tree and you're my three and when you burn, now I'm free to find me... number four and number four can marry me. Bomb, bomb, bomb... Just like me, final tree, you're lovely, but you're lonely... I will clone thee, little tree."

Anathallo offered us their amazing five bedroom loft once their lease is up in March. It's in the best location, next to a ton of job opportunities (so many fun, cute places!) and, rent split is  only $220!!!! It is such a good deal, I hardly think I can refuse it. I think I am ready for a change in scenery anyway.

I feel I will update with something cool I did.


I was in Ann Arbor this weekend for Rock for Daftuar. It was actually a lot of fun. I wasn't so sure how comfortable I would feel drinking in such a large city at a house party doubling as a show where I planned on knowing, oh, three people? (Those three people being the friends/band I traveled with that would be playing.) Come to find out, I ran into people I haven't seen in almost 2 years! Old friends from all over Michigan, it was absolutely wild. (I never realized how many people moved to/around Ann Arbor!) Once comfortable, I downed two sparks, a pabst and basically made myself at home on top of Josh's car when I wasn't spilling myself over the porch kicking my boots over people's heads below. I spent the vast majority of my night with Dustin, Lauren and Casey (None of whom I have seen in FOREVER!) I lost my phone (twice!) but managed to find it on the next door neighbors porch. I rekindled old friendships with people whom I used to care immensely about (Maybe crushing on future art hipsters who would be "too cool for school" wasn't exactly my strongpoint...) and making new, awesome friends with people who shared a mutual friend with me. I will admit, I was only impressed with a few bands (and I'll admit, I only paid attention to two of them.) but it was entirely too much fun. I was two blocks from downtown, so I took a few walks and made a few calls before my phone died, and finally ended up back in Mt. Pleasant by 7AM!

1) Haircut!
2) Envy
3) Hungs with Kakes NaMore
4) Organized!
5) Sleeeeeeeeeeepyhead
6) Bat chase.

Lj is boring, snoring.

"it's only this fucked up i start realizing all this living is just dying and if these are my friends, if this is my home, if this is how i spend my nights, how i communicate, and demonstrate a love of life. my eyes roll into the back of my head, if these are the last words that i ever said. no, i'm not ready to die just yet."
Life has been very good to me. I pretty much get whatever I want and I'm constantly exchanging smiles and laughs with good people. To be honest, that's all I really need.
I'm just, a very happy girl that knows what she wants. Oh, and who can't wait 'til Summer '08 FUCK!
I'm so ready for the summer! Va-va-voom!

No, I love life. My short hair is a success, I haven't seen my bestfriend in so long but that's okay because we love eachother very,very much and, you know, she's a very busy bee. Girl Talk on Saturday, I've had lots of money lately and it's nice but I want it all the time.
Rambling sentence, because I just can't put enough effort into updating this properly.
Kaelen and I might be going to GrlTlk in Chicago.

I love my record collection. revert back to analog.


HAY GIRL HAAAY

I got a darling new dress for my birthday/new years!
It should be here within the next couple days. I saw it on project runway and fell in looovvveee!
Things are going well. The only thing that sucks is Zack got out of jail, and I missed seeing him before he returned to saginaw by ONE HOUR! I absolutely hate myself for sleeping in. I'm tired all the tiiimmeee. PEACE!
Always, always always happy & ready to ring in the new year!
<center>it's cool, we can still be friends
